	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102513509516662><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=10154&mid=102513509516662>I would love this item=)</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=10154&mid=102513509516662#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=106989><span id= >Ashliin the Charming</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jun 26th 7:54 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm a lvl 54 enchanter, and I guess I'm doing something really wrong, because my int/cha doesn't come close to 255 even buffed.&nbsp;&nbsp;I run at about 207 int/ 157 cha unbuffed.  I would love to have this belt.  For those that say it is easy to get int/cha items...make an enchanter, and go shopping, not with enough money to buy the most uber items either.  It is tough to find int/cha items, yes there are a few out there, but even those low ones cost good money.  It seems like most items that you see are int/cha combo, can't even be used by an enchanter.  It amazes me, how many of the int/cha items I can't use, but a Necro can, like they want the cha.  Personally, even if I weren't an enchanter, I would have to say that this would be the best class to give this item too, with the exception of MAYBE a Bard, or a Shaman (because {and I know this is still a controversy} the higher a shamans cha the better thier chances of not being resisted are on debuff {my husband has a lvl 52 shaman, and we have tested this many times, and IMO, cha is a neccesity for a shaman as well).  So, even though there are a combination of stats that would be good for any class, I think that it would most benefit an enchanter, bard or shaman.  I also would be extremely upset to see a raid leader allow any others besides those three roll on this item.  Of course i'm sure that most of those at this level, hunting this type of zone, and leading a raid big enough to take Rumblecrush down, would have the knowledge as to who this item would most benefit, and set some rules here, as to who gets to roll.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ashliin Breezenby<br>54th Enchantress<br>&lt;High Council of Mystic Defiance&gt;</td></tr>
